            <h2>Who are we?</h2>
            <p class="quizText">We are a group of computer and cognitive science students from the University of California San Diego. This website project is part of a Human Computer interaction design class we are taking. We wanted to make a site relating to the idea of citizen science, which is the idea that the regular community at large can come together to become like scientists and contribute to science. This is a plant identifying site around the idea of citizen science. Our goal with this site is to provide a plant identifier that, unlike other identifiers, stimulates the user, making them think and become a scientist in the process of identifying their plant, while at the same time contributing to scientific data on plants, which can help ecologists and other plant scientists.  

